               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-215-person1905">
                  HENRY 
                  OLDHAM
               <interp inst="t18300415-215-person1905" type="surname" value="OLDHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-person1905" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-person1905" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18300415-215-viclabel1195" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18300415-215-crimeloc1196">Crown, in Long-acre</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-crimeloc1196" type="placeName" value="Crown, in Long-acre"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-crimeloc1196" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-215-off1193 t18300415-215-crimeloc1196"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-215-victim1904 t18300415-215-viclabel1195"></join> -On the 26th of February, in the afternoon, I missed this spoon; the prisoner had been in the bar all day - I missed the money in the evening; the prisoner had slept there the night before - I missed three half-crowns from the till; I had gone out of the bar while he was there - I had not observed what silver was in my till, but I know the half-crowns were there; I missed two of them first - I then went out of the bar, and when I returned I found the till unlocked, and the other one gone; the till was locked when I went out - the spoons were taken from the bar parlour.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. CRESWELL. Q. Was he not drinking all the night before? A. He had drank a little in the evening, some beer and some half-and-half; I did not see him drink any spirits or wine - he did not fall asleep in my bar; he came there on the evening of the 23rd - he was not very drunk; he frequented the house before I came there, which is fifteen months ago; I believe he is respectably connected; I lock my till when I go out, and take the key - I know there were half-crowns,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150100"></xptr>shillings and sixpences in the till, but no crown pieces; I cannot say how many persons came in while he was there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-215-person1906">
                  WILLIAM 
                  CLARK
               <interp inst="t18300415-215-person1906" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-person1906" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-person1906" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the house at a quarter after eleven o'clock; Mrs. Oldham had been saying she had lost some money and a tea-spoon - I said, "Who have you had in your bar?" she said, "No one but Mr. Brooks;" soon after Mr. Brooks came into the tap-room, and laid down - Mr. Oldham's brother-in-law was there: Mr. Oldham then came in, and said he had lost the money and the spoon; he saw the prisoner there, he rubbed his hand down him, and found these bottles and this spoon on him - I had a very severe struggle with him; he made very great resistance; there were three half-crowns, two shillings, one sixpence, 3s. in copper, and four farthings on him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Had you been there the night before? A. I do not recollect; I had reason to recollect that evening, as I got a brace of very handsome black eyes; I gave him as good as he sent, and a little better: I cannot say whether he was drunk the night before.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-215-verdict1197" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-verdict1197" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 27. - <rs id="t18300415-215-punish1198" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300415-215-punish1198" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-215-defend1902 t18300415-215-punish1198"></join>
               Confined Six Months
            </rs>.</p>
